---
// Slice 2b — unified, URL-driven SEARCH + FILTER + card-grid results, all
// client-side against the Pagefind index on cdn. Homepage: empty = the static
// server-rendered feed (#static-feed); a query OR any facet → Pagefind cards.
//
// 2026-06-07 fixes (all root-caused live, not guessed):
//  - FREEZE: pf.filters() costs ~2.4s on the 51k index; it was called on EVERY
//    keystroke (inside run) → multi-second main-thread lock per char. Now called
//    ONCE at init to build the facet UI; run() never calls it again.
//  - MULTI-SELECT returned 0: Pagefind treats an ARRAY filter value as AND
//    (`type:[news,pi_circular]` = both → 0). For OR-within-a-group we must use
//    `{any:[...]}` (measured: any → 29,961 = News 18,227 + P&I 11,734). Done.
//  - SORT: results were relevance-ordered (a 2-week-old item could top "News").
//    When there's NO text query (pure browse/filter) we sort by date desc, so
//    newest is first. Needs data-pagefind-sort="date" on article pages (added).
//  - SOURCE is a dropdown (57 values) not a chip wall — matches v1; also removes
//    the per-keystroke 57-chip rebuild.
//  - Phrase search already works (Pagefind native): "exact phrase" in quotes.
//  - SYNONYM EXPANSION (2026-06-10): the typed text is matched to a SYNONYMS key —
//    exact, else the shortest key that STARTS WITH it ("speed" → "speed claim"). Its
//    related terms open in a checkbox DROPDOWN under the box (auto-opens on a new
//    match, closes on outside-click, reopen via the button) — ALL checked by default;
//    only CHECKED terms are searched alongside the raw query (live). Streams are
//    k-way merged in pure date order, deduped by url. A quoted query gets no panel.
//
// Self-contained; does NOT touch Search.astro (header search on other pages).
// Card classes are COPIED from CompactArticleCard.astro so Tailwind (which does
// NOT scan strings built in this is:inline script) has already emitted them.

const base = (import.meta.env.PUBLIC_PAGEFIND_BASE ?? '').replace(/\/$/, '');

// Synonym / related-terms map for client-side query expansion (2026-06-10).
// When the typed query EXACTLY equals a key (lowercased, not a quoted phrase),
// the client also searches the listed related terms and merges the results —
// so "PSC" also surfaces "port state control" articles. Directed (key → values),
// used as authored; not auto-reversed. Multi-word related terms are searched as
// exact phrases at runtime. Shown as toggleable chips (all on by default); only
// the user-selected terms are searched. Maritime acronyms + cargo / vessel-type /
// charter-party / P&I / port / performance-claim / narcotics domains.
